A catalogue of the library of Mr. Henry Cook, painter, deceased which will be sold by auction at his late dwelling house in Bloomsbury-Square, near King-Street in Bloomsbury, on Monday, the 30th instant, at three afternoon / by John Bullord. Cook, Henry, 1642-1700. Bullord, John.
[2], 6 p.
s.n., [London : 1669?]
"Catalogues to be had at Mr. Parkers at the Unicorn under the Royal Exchange, Mr. Buck, near the Temple, Mr. Barnes, in the Pall-Mall, bookseller, and at the place of sale" Place and date of publication from Wing. Reproduction of original in British Library.
